article.description: Corbin Miller scored a season-high 18, on a career-high six 3-pointers, Zena Edosomwan added 11 points and grabbed 12 rebounds, and Harvard beat Ryerson 73-57 Tuesday night.
article.headline: Harvard downs Ryerson 73-57
article.story: CAMBRIDGE, Mass. -- Corbin Miller scored a season-high 18, on a career-high six 3-pointers, Zena Edosomwan added 11 points and grabbed 12 rebounds, and Harvard beat Ryerson 73-57 Tuesday night. Evan Cummins scored 12 points, Weisner Perez grabbed 13 rebounds and Agunwa Okolie had 10 boards for the Crimson (8-8), who outrebounded Ryerson 58-32. Ryerson, of Toronto, Ontario, Canada, led early, but Perez hit a go-ahead jumper amid a 10-2 run for the Crimson. Miller hit two 3-pointers during a 13-3 spurt and Harvard led 38-23 at halftime. The Rams traded baskets with the Crimson in the second half, but failed to gain ground. Patrick Steeves' layup with 3:16 to go put Harvard up 69-52 and the Rams got no closer than 15 the rest of the way. Jean-Victor Mukama and Aaron Best scored 12 apiece for the Rams, who play in the Ontario University Athletics league. Harvard will conclude non-conference play on Saturday, Jan. 16 at Howard.
